>found some pretty creative repairs and patches here and there. I guess
>my only real complaint is with the wiring -- why do people refuse to
>use wire connectors?

Some shoddy wiring (around the radio only) is the one kludge I indulge
myself in. Soldering proper connectors and so forth is just more work that
I
think the radio is worth, when twisting wires together and covering them up

with masking tape does the job just fine. I keep telling myself "next time
it's warm, I'll solder them proper."

